subSubSection.paragraph:
Watersipora atrofusca
(
Busk, 1856
)

(
Fig. 10
; 
Table 2
), known from Mazatlan (
Mexico
), resembles 

W. cucullata

in colony shape but differs in having a smaller, almost circular orifice and in lacking intrazooidal septula.
